Here's the code for reading data from an Excel file using Python:

```python
import pandas as pd

def read_excel(file_name):
    df = pd.read_excel(file_name)
    return df
```

This function takes in the name of the excel file and returns a DataFrame object which can be used to manipulate or analyze the data.

To use this function, simply call it with the filename as an argument:

```python
df = read_excel('filename.xlsx')
print(df)
```
This will print out the contents of the Excel file in a DataFrame format.
